  "body": "Getting a kubectl context/credentials through e.g. GKE creates an entry in ~/.kubeconfig with a lengthy name: gke_projectname_zone_cluster-name.\r\n\r\nIt would be amazing to be able to rename the context via kubectl instead of manually in .kubeconfig \r\nBefore:\r\n```\r\nCURRENT   NAME   CLUSTER AUTHINFO NAMESPACE\r\n* gke_projectname_zone_cluster-name gke_projectname_zone_cluster-name gke_projectname_zone_cluster-name gke_projectname_zone_cluster-name\r\n```\r\n--> `kubectl config rename-context k8s-is-awesome-cluster`\r\n\r\nAfter:\r\n```\r\nCURRENT   NAME   CLUSTER AUTHINFO NAMESPACE\r\n* k8s-is-awesome-cluster gke_projectname_zone_cluster-name gke_projectname_zone_cluster-name gke_projectname_zone_cluster-name\r\n```\r\n@kubernetes/kubectl",
